[SN]TITLE[SN]
Three escape injury as pipe bomb is thrown into yard of house

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
Three people have escaped injury after a pipe bomb was thrown into the rear yard of a house in Londonderry.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Two adults and a child were in the property on Ebrington Street when the device was thrown shortly after midnight on Friday morning.
Residents had to leave their homes in the surrounding area as Army bomb disposal experts defused the device.
A controlled explosion was carried out just after 05:30 GMT. Emerson Street and Bond Street have now reopened.
